        <Parent_String>African by general distribution [300263055], African by cultural or regional designation [300121001], African (general, continental cultures) [300015647], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The collective style and culture of various African peoples whose adult males grow to less than 59 inches (150 cm) in average height, and who live in Cameroon, Equatorial Guinea, Gabon, Democratic Republic of Congo, Congo Republic, Central African Republic, Rwanda, and Burundi. Use of "Pygmy" for a culture is considered pejorative; where possible use instead the most specific name for the subgroup.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para describir trabajos producidos por ciertos pueblos africanos que viven en Camerún, Guinea Ecuatorial, Gabón, República Democrática de Congo, República de Congo, República de África Central, Ruanda y Burundi. El uso de "Pigmeo" es peyorativo; donde sea posible use en cambio un nombre más específico para el subgrupo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken om werken te beschrijven van bepaalde Afrikaanse volkeren die leven in Kameroen, Equatoriaal-Guinea, de Democratische Republiek Congo, Congo, de Centraal-Afrikaanse Republiek, Rwanda en Burundi. De term Pygmee heeft soms een negatieve bijklank. Waar mogelijk verdient het gebruik van de specifieke naam van een subgroep de voorkeur.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052519/Landendocumentatie (KIT)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>某些分佈在喀麥隆、赤道幾內亞、加彭、剛果民主共和國、剛果共和國、中非共和國、盧安達、蒲隆地的非洲民族所創作的作品。「俾格米」一詞帶有貶意，故盡可能使用特定且明確的族群名稱為宜。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
